<ns218:section xmlns:ns218="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.jboss.introduction.highLevelOverview">

  <ns219:title xmlns:ns219="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">High-level overview of JBoss</ns219:title>
  <ns220:para xmlns:ns220="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
     JBoss is an open-source implementation of an EJB application server which supports
     full J2EE application development. 
     JBoss has repetitatively obtained the second place the Java World award for best J2EE
     application server (after BEA's WebLogic but before IBM's Websphere).
     It's core elements are    
    <ns221:itemizedlist xmlns:ns221="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns222:listitem xmlns:ns222="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns223:para xmlns:ns223="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        The JBossServer which is an implementation of an EJB container and application
        server. 
      </ns223:para></ns222:listitem>
      <ns224:listitem xmlns:ns224="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns225:para xmlns:ns225="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        An infrastructure which implements the Java Management Extension (JPX) API which
        provides the mechanism for attaching end exchanging components to the application server.
      </ns225:para></ns224:listitem>
    </ns221:itemizedlist>
  </ns220:para>  
  <ns226:para xmlns:ns226="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    In addition to these core elements, JBoss supplies a range of support components
    which are added to JBoss. Through JMX one can simple replace any of these components with
    other components developed by other teams or vendors and one can easily add further
    components. The standard components shipped with JBoss are
    <ns227:itemizedlist xmlns:ns227="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns228:listitem xmlns:ns228="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns229:para xmlns:ns229="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JBossMQ for JMS messaging. </ns229:para>
      </ns228:listitem>
      <ns230:listitem xmlns:ns230="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns231:para xmlns:ns231="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JBossCMP for container managed persistence (CMP). </ns231:para>
      </ns230:listitem>
      <ns232:listitem xmlns:ns232="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns233:para xmlns:ns233="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JBossTX for JTA/JTS transactions. </ns233:para>
      </ns232:listitem>
      <ns234:listitem xmlns:ns234="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns235:para xmlns:ns235="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JBossCX for JCA connectivity. </ns235:para>
      </ns234:listitem>
      <ns236:listitem xmlns:ns236="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns237:para xmlns:ns237="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JBossSX for JAAS based security. </ns237:para>
      </ns236:listitem>
      <ns238:listitem xmlns:ns238="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns239:para xmlns:ns239="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">An integration layer for web containers like Tomcat and Jetty.</ns239:para>
      </ns238:listitem>
    </ns227:itemizedlist>
  </ns226:para>  
</ns218:section>